original: Leffler, Svea Margareta, tandläkare, Brålanda, f. 20/6/78 i Bolstad, Älvsb. 1., av godsäg. Olof Lars-son o. Carolina Andersson. G. 07 m. Håkan Anders Leffler. Barn: Greta f. 08, tandl, Håkan Albert 09, övermaskinist, deläg. i Fartygsreparationer Leffler o. Gre-bert, Gbg, Elisabeth 11, civ:ing. v. Chalmers provnranst. kem. avd., Gbg, Björn 13, inneh. av skjortfabr. Nero, Varberg, Nils 14, agronom, Hans 16, hovr :fiskal, e. o. not. v. Gbgs råd-liusr. — Mog:ex. i Vänersborg 96, tandl. 01, stud. i Berlin f. prof. W. Sachs samt spec:stud. betr. porslins-inlägg f. dr A. Kö]^bitz, dr J. Grün-iberg o. prof. Marmlock. Prakt, i Gbg 01-28, i Kungsbacka 28-32 o. i Horred 32-47, i Brålanda sed. 47. Ledare för kurs i porslinsinlägg v. Deutsches Zahnärzte-Haus i Berlin 23, ett flertal föredrag och de-monstr. betr. porslinsinlägg o. por-slinssmältn. Skr.: Die Porzellanfül-lung (Corresp. Blått f. Zahnärzte 22), über den Wert der Porzellan-Einla-gen (dito 22) etc.
translated: Leffler, Svea Margareta, dentist, Brålanda, b. 20/6/78 in Bolstad, Älvsb. 1st district, daughter of estate owner Olof Larsson and Carolina Andersson. Married in 1907 to Håkan Anders Leffler. Children: Greta b. 1908, dentist, Håkan Albert b. 1909, chief engineer, co-owner of Fartygsreparationer Leffler and Gre-bert in Gothenburg, Elisabeth b. 1911, civil engineer at Chalmers research institute in the chemical division, Gothenburg, Björn b. 1913, owner of shirt factory Nero, Varberg, Nils b. 1914, agronomist, Hans b. 1916, court prosecutor, acting notary at Gothenburg City Court. Passed the dental examination in Vänersborg in 1896, graduated as a dentist in 1901, studied in Berlin under Professor W. Sachs and specialized in porcelain inlays under Dr. A. Kö]^bitz, Dr. J. Grün-iberg, and Professor Marmlock. Worked in Gothenburg from 1901 to 1928, in Kungsbacka from 1928 to 1932, and in Horred from 1932 to 1947, and in Brålanda since 1947. Led a course on porcelain inlays at Deutsches Zahnärzte-Haus in Berlin in 1923, gave numerous lectures and demonstrations on porcelain inlays and porcelain fusion. Written works include "Die Porzellanfüllung" (Corresp. Blått f. Zahnärzte 22), "über den Wert der Porzellan-Einlagen" (dito 22), etc.
